<pdd-reason>Deterministic validator and applicator for approved interactive checkup prompt patches.</pdd-reason>
<pdd-interface>
{
  "type": "module",
  "module": {
    "classes": [
      {"name": "ApplyFindingRecord", "kind": "dataclass"},
      {"name": "ApplyRunResult", "kind": "dataclass"}
    ],
    "functions": [
      {"name": "apply_approved_patches", "signature": "(patches: Sequence[ApprovedPatch], *, repo_root: Path, original_target: str, dry_run: bool = False, interactive: bool = True, strict: bool = False, choices_by_finding: Mapping[str, int] | None = None) -> ApplyRunResult", "returns": "ApplyRunResult"}
    ]
  }
}
</pdd-interface>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_interactive_session_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_prompt_main_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Goal
Write `pdd/checkup_prompt_apply.py`.

% Requirements
- Validate approved patch kind and target path before any write.
- Allow prompt source targets including `pdd/prompts/**/*.prompt`, excluding `*_LLM.prompt`.
- Continue forbidding tests, generated/context paths, implementation files under `pdd/`, absolute paths, and traversal outside the repository root.
- In `--dry-run`, record accepted/rejected patches and write the apply log, but do not mutate files or create backups.
- For real applies, create backups under `.pdd/evidence/checkups/backups/<run_id>/`, write atomically, then run a deterministic postflight checkup.
- Any rejected approved patch must remain inspectable with `status="rejected"`, include a reason, return a non-zero exit code, and must not report `postflight_status="pass"` unless all approved patches were valid and postflight passed.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Rejected approvals fail honestly
If any approved patch is rejected, `ApplyRunResult.exit_code` MUST be non-zero and `postflight_status` MUST NOT be `pass`.

R2 - Prompt source allowlist
`pdd/prompts/**/*.prompt` MAY be repaired, while `pdd/**/*.py`, `tests/**`, generated artifacts, absolute paths, and traversal targets MUST be rejected.

R3 - Dry-run is read-only
When `dry_run=True`, no prompt bytes or backup files may be written.
</contract_rules>

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/checkup_prompt_apply.py`
